If you do not have a custom trained model yet, you can start with the
default YOLOv8 nano model (`yolov8n.pt`) from Ultralytics for testing.
Just download it and place it in this folder, then update the
`YOLO_MODEL_PATH` value in your `.env` file to match the filename.

2. **Uploaded complaint images**
When users upload photos through the "Report Issue" page, the app
automatically creates a subfolder here called `uploaded_images/`
and saves all uploaded photos inside it. You do not need to create
this subfolder yourself — the app does it automatically.

## Notes

- Do not commit large model files or user-uploaded images to GitHub.
These are already excluded in the `.gitignore` file.
- If you train your own custom YOLOv8 model on civic issue images
(potholes, garbage, water leaks, broken streetlights, damaged roads),
simply place the resulting `.pt` file in this folder and update the
`.env` file accordingly.
